) called for a banking restriction last year on all financial institutions offering services to cryptocurrency exchanges, the countrys crypto ecosystem saw its first acquisition with global crypto exchange Binance acquiring peer-to-peer crypto exchange WazirX launched in 2018. Majority of Indian startups including Bitcoin India, Koinex, Zebpay etc. closed operations or moved outside India or launched P2P platforms to sustain. However, WazirX had launched the P2P exchange   auto-matching P2P engine to help traders to convert Indian Rupees to crypto and vice versa, right after the ban. The move (RBI ban) proved to be a game-changer and made the platform cheapest, fastest, and simplest way to trade cryptocurrencies using INR in India, the company said.
